WHO SHOULD ATTEND:

Researchers and practitioners in end user development, visual languages,
object-orientation and process/workflow modelling.  Information system
managers and end users development officers.  Software technology
vendors, in particular vendors of visual programming systems and
object-oriented development systems.


HOW TO APPLY:

Two types of submissions are invited:
(1) position papers of no more than 2000 words;
(2) state of the art review papers  of no more than 4000 words

Send the submission plus a short self description to the workshop
organisers by the deadline.  The submissions will be reviewed.  The
accepted papers will be published by the conference organisers.

The preferred mode of communication is e-mail.  If your application has
not been acknowledged by the organisers within three days of the
submission, please re-submit it.


